<DocsLayout
  title="Iter Variable"
  description="Using the iter variable for sequential data"
  breadcrumbs={breadcrumbs}
  headings={headings}
>
  <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>

  <p>
    The <code>iter</code> variable represents the current iteration index (0-based) and is useful for creating sequential IDs or patterns:
  </p>

  <pre set:html={`<code>gens {
  func id() {
    return iter + 1  // Creates 1, 2, 3, 4...
  }

  func username() {
    return "user" + String(iter)  // user0, user1, user2...
  }
}</code>`}></pre>

  <h2 id="examples">Examples</h2>

  <h3>Sequential IDs</h3>

  <pre set:html={`<code>func userId() {
  return iter + 1000  // Start from 1000
}</code>`}></pre>

  <h3>Pattern-based Generation</h3>

  <pre set:html={`<code>func category() {
  if iter % 3 == 0 {
    return "Electronics"
  } else if iter % 3 == 1 {
    return "Clothing"
  } else {
    return "Food"
  }
}</code>`}></pre>

